{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"de5bf782-9e1b-489e-9024-1ecdef635c23","content":"Use the `--filter` flag with `&` to combine conditions:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Smoke&ClassName~Integration\"\n```\n\n- `Category=Smoke` — matches tests with `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]`\n- `~` — \"contains\" operator on `ClassName`\n- `&` — logical AND, combining both into one expression","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"da38d248-0f11-49ef-880a-729ed4ea105d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to construct a single combined filter expression for `dotnet test` that:\n1. Runs only tests with the \"Smoke\" category/trait\n2. From classes whose name contains \"Integration\"\n\nThey want this as a single `--filter` expression rather than separate flags.\n\nIn xUnit v3 with `dotnet test`, you use the `--filter` option with MSTest-style filter expressions. The syntax supports:\n- `FullyQualifiedName` — matches the full test name\n- `DisplayName` — matches the display name\n- `Category` — matches traits (in xUnit, `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]`)\n\n\n- `ClassName` — matches the class name\n\nYou can combine conditions with `&` (AND) and `|` (OR), and use `~` for contains operations. So the filter expression would combine both conditions with AND, requiring tests to have the Smoke category AND be in a class containing \"Integration\".","outputTokens":352,"requestId":"BD2C:17E76D:20C5153:256B8BA:6A07E171"},"id":"78b6bd4a-b53b-491c-9008-c60697e1aa38","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:16:09.956Z","parentId":"1fd7f125-609f-4f03-887f-ab233d801f79"}
